==========================================
Whisper TFLite encoder-only swap for robot daemon STT
Date: 2026-04-19 (evening pass)
Device: Pixel 6 (1B291FDF600260), Android ARM64-v8a
Laptop: x86_64 Linux, tflite_runtime 2.14.0, torch 2.11, whisper 20240930
==========================================

GOAL
----
Unblock the TFLite STT path left in a broken state in the morning log
(logs/whisper_tflite_swap_2026-04-19.log). The community-ported
nyadla-sys/whisper-tiny.en.tflite has a non-functional baked-in greedy
decoder (emits only prologue tokens then EOT). Approach chosen:

  Approach 1 (encoder-only TFLite + laptop pytorch decoder):
    - /tmp/tflite-models/whisper_enc_tiny_en_fp32.tflite  (33 MB, fp32)
      input (1, 3000, 80) f32 mel -> output (1, 1500, 384) f32 audio_features
    - openai-whisper's pytorch decoder with DecodingTask,
      _get_audio_features monkey-patched to return the TFLite output.
      DecodingOptions(task='transcribe', language='en',
                      without_timestamps=True) — so we don't need to
      fiddle with forced_decoder_ids at export time.

This worked on the first try. Approach 2 (re-export full graph) was not
needed.

INTEGRATION
-----------
scripts/whisper_tflite_runner.py rewritten:
  - DEFAULT mode now: --model-mode encoder-only
  - LEGACY mode kept: --model-mode full (the broken nyadla-sys graph)
  - Module-level caches (_CACHED_INTERPRETER, _CACHED_WHISPER_MODEL) so
    in-process callers reuse state across calls.
  - CLI API preserved: takes WAV, prints transcript on stdout; --json
    still emits {transcript, wall_s, backend, model, timings_ms}.
  - demo/robot_daemon.py NOT touched (per constraints).

